  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide one Mechanised Borehole to Bongo Hospital</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is meant to provide one mechanised water supply system to Bongo District Hospital in Upper East Region, Ghana. The hospital is an 85-bed capacity, serving about 134 communities with total population size of 84,545. The hospital has a history of recording frequent water shortages hence the maternity and surgical wards do not get frequent water supply thus resulting in frequent deaths and high rates of referral cases of minor surgical and caesarean operations to the regional hospital.</narrative>
  </description>
